page.title: 02NATURE IN NASSINGTON.
page.content: There is a lot of interesting nature in our block.Most of the land is farmland so there could be much more. The River Nene has lots of water plants including lilies,rushes and reeds with fish such as eels,pike, perch and roach.There are 10 ponds with much life such as daphnia,water spiders,and beetles.Some have frogs, newts and toads.Small woods,remnants of Rockingham Forest,have oak, silver birch,elm and hawthorn.Many elms have died because of Dutch Elm Disease. Hedgerows,mainly of hawthorn have lots of rabbits,pheasants and their chicks. Birds are nesting busily.There is a small owl in the Holm Oak next to school.Owl pellets we gathered had bones and claws in them.Some villagers belong to the Northamptonshire Trust for Nature Conservation.They help to look after our wildlife.
